Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine light pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 12 Name Timodikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0221.28.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0998)
